Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

G7 — expose marked_by on attendance records
  /mobile/attendance now eager-loads markedBy:id,name and includes
  marked_by in the response for both teacher (staff_attendances) and
  student/parent (attendances) branches.

G6 — leave-balance enforcement on apply
  applyLeave (student) and applyStaffLeave both now check days_allowed
  vs days_used in the current academic year before creating the row.
  If the new request would exceed the balance, returns 422 with a
  helpful message + balance breakdown. days_allowed=0 means unlimited
  (skip the check).

Bonus fix while I was in there — leaveTypes (student) was using
SQLite-only julianday() syntax in selectRaw, which silently returned 0
on MySQL production deployments so balance always looked full. Now
counts days in PHP using Carbon::diffInDays, matching the staff
implementation.

G1 — staff punch accepts remarks
  staffPunchClockIn / staffPunchClockOut now both validate an optional
  remarks (max 255). Clock-in stores it on the row; clock-out appends
  to the existing remarks with " · " separator so both halves of the
  day are visible.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
